trace.verification_evidence:
{
  "red_failure_evidence": "BEFORE THIS CELL: the gateway config had eight settings and no notion of an agent preset — git show HEAD:src/config/mod.rs shows Config with bind_addr, herdr_session, allowed_roots, poll_interval_ms, herdr_protocol, static_dir, herdr_socket, telegram_chat_id and nothing else, so there was no way to configure what an agent-start row on the phone would run. PRE-CHANGE CHECK THAT FAILED: cargo test --quiet --lib -- presets_ | grep -qE 'test result: ok. ([6-9]|[1-9][0-9]+) passed' on the untouched tree printed 'running 0 tests / test result: ok. 0 passed; 201 filtered out' and the guard grep exited 1. A SECOND RED, DELIBERATELY INDUCED: the worker was required to prove rather than reason about the CONFIG_FIELDS guard, so agent_presets was temporarily removed from that allowlist and presets_survive_a_doctor_repair_write was run alone — it failed with 'agent_presets must survive a field repair, not be dropped, left: 0, right: 1' — then the entry was restored and it passed. A THIRD RED arose unplanned and blocked the cell: adding a ninth entry to CONFIG_FIELDS shifted the doctor menu's stop index from 12 to 13, and seven existing doctor tests hardcoded 12, so they selected a field's edit prompt instead of stopping and died on real stdin.",
  "green_evidence": {
    "command": "cargo test --quiet && cargo fmt --all --check && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo test --lib -- presets_ | grep -qE 'test result: ok. ([6-9]|[1-9][0-9]+) passed'",
    "run_by": "orchestrator, independently, after the worker reported",
    "output": "cargo test --quiet: 213 passed, 0 failed (201 before this cell). fmt --all --check: silent. clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings: silent. presets_-only: 12 passed, 0 failed, 201 filtered out. Guard grep exit code: 0."
  },
  "behavior_change_description": "The config gained agent_presets, a list of {label, argv} entries defaulting to empty so a gateway without presets still boots. A preset with an empty label, an empty argv, an empty first argv element, or a label another preset already uses fails config load through a dedicated ConfigError variant naming the entry by index and label, collected into the existing multi-error path so several bad presets report together rather than one per run. agent_presets is registered in CONFIG_FIELDS with a matching validator, so a doctor-driven field repair preserves it instead of deleting it.",
  "observable_difference": "An operator can declare the agent rows the phone will offer, and a malformed one is refused at startup with the offending entry named — rather than surfacing later as a row that does nothing on a phone away from the machine.",
  "regression_guard": "12 presets_ tests. presets_survive_a_doctor_repair_write is the one that matters most and was proven to fail when the CONFIG_FIELDS entry is absent. presets_absent_defaults_to_empty_list keeps the field optional. presets_multiple_bad_presets_reported_together keeps the multi-error path. In the doctor tests the stop-menu index is now derived from CONFIG_FIELDS.len() in a helper instead of hardcoded, and the menu-coverage test asserts against CONFIG_FIELDS rather than a literal count, so the next setting added costs nothing.",
  "reviewer_note": "The cell was correctly reported BLOCKED mid-flight: adding a ninth config field breaks any test that hardcodes a doctor menu position, so 'add to CONFIG_FIELDS', 'keep all existing tests green' and 'do not touch src/doctor/' were mutually exclusive as originally scoped. That was an orchestrator planning error — the cells were split by module when the coupling is by count. Scope was widened to the doctor test fixtures, with the instruction to derive the index rather than bump the literal, so the fragility is removed rather than moved. Filed as friction. Two stale doc comments in src/doctor/edit.rs still claim eight fields; deliberately left to the next cell, which also owns the same claim in docs/specs/doctor.md."
}
